<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 12:49AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT WESTERN ELKHART AND SOUTHEASTERN
ST. JOSEPH COUNTIES THROUGH 145 AM EDT...
At 1249 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wakarusa, or near Mishawaka, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM EDT for
north central Indiana.</instruction>
